      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/47e85d/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2022-02-16T12:54:28.824Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>I train on the Elite Diretto XRT trainer and I noticed that during the implementation of training plans with a set cadence above 75 rpm, the set power constantly oscillates (about) -20 W to +10 W compared to the set one, despite the fact that I try to keep the cadence evenly (I use in the background with a beat-beating metronome app).<br>\nIt is extremely difficult to train with a given power.</p>\n<p>As soon as I start training with a cadence of no more than 75 rpm, the power is kept evenly.</p>\n<p>I did not notice such a power oscillation during training using the OneLap application.</p>\n<p>The trainer is calibrated.</p>",
