      "created_at": "2022-02-17T12:40:06.035Z",
      "cooked": "<p>This thread might be talking about the same problem (at the bottom)</p>\n<p>I just created this new topic to address this issue.</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"1402\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/samoramobile/48/1935_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/t/erg-problems-related-to-slope-mode/1402\">ERG problems related to slope mode</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/resolved-bugs-and-issues/33\"><span data-category-id=\"33\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #3AB54A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Resolved Bugs and Issues</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    I\u2019ve been having problems for a few weeks, where everything starts well, but after a few minutes I can\u2019t get the power set in the training, besides that there are a lot of oscillations in the power data, today I tested everything again but this time with another Tablet and other heart rate sensor. \nIn this space of time I used my Wahoo Roam, \nEdge 830, F\u00e9nix 5X, Rouvy, Zwift and today for the first time the RGT Cycling, and in none of them I had the same problems, so I come to the conclusion tha\u2026\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
